  "prompt": "What does \"last activity\" mean on Skype?",
  "response": "In Skype, \"Last Activity\" refers to the most recent time the user was active on the platform. This can include actions such as sending or reading messages, making or receiving calls, or simply being online. It helps users understand when someone was last active on Skype.\n\nHere\u2019s what it typically indicates:\n\n1. **Online/Active**: The user is currently online and actively using Skype.\n2. **Recently Active**: The user was online within the last few minutes or hours.\n3. **Specific Time**: If the user is offline, it shows the exact time they were last active.\n\nThis feature is useful for knowing whether someone is available for interaction or when they might return. Note that the visibility of \"Last Activity\" depends on the user\u2019s privacy settings\u2014they can choose to hide this information if they prefer.",
